    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="406"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Special Assistant</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>, and
                        the President’s Reply</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d406fn1">According to <persName corresp="#p_SRE1"
                            >Sherwood</persName>, p. 796, these messages were exchanged near the end
                        of the tripartite luncheon meeting of December 1, 1943 (<hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_585">p. 585</ref>). For a facsimile
                        reproduction of the messages, which were handwritten, see <persName
                            corresp="#p_SRE1">Sherwood</persName>, p. 797.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-01">December 1,
                            1943</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. President</hi>: What do you think of letting the
                    Russians give dinner tonight—your last chance at Russian food</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>OK but I have to leave <hi rend="italic">early</hi> as we sleep at the
                        camp.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">FDR</persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
